commit.message: Use @v4 actions to avoid warnings. Some tweaks to the build matrix.
Let cabal-fix do its magic + small tweaks
Add GHCs 9.6.2 and 9.8.0 to Haskell CI, update 9.2 and 9.4 to latest
Add TypeOperators for GHC 9.4, add 9.4 to Haskell CI
Use the right command to generate GitHub actions. :-}

Somehow GHC 9.2.1 seems to unsupported in GitHub Actions.

The workflow errored out with "Invalid workflow file" for the line
"- compiler: ghc-9.2.1".  No idea what's going on, let's remove that
version for now.

Explictly mark module as Safe (or Trustworthy)

- The stm is Trustworthy since 2.3
- There is no reason to support transformers older than 0.3,
  as it's the oldest version bundled with any GHC
Update .gitignore to better work with a cabal v2- workflow
